# English Civil War

Part of the [Wars of the Three Kingdoms](/Wars_of_the_Three_Kingdoms)

The [Battle of Naseby](/Battle_of_Naseby), fought on 14 June 1645, stands as a pivotal [Parliamentarian](/Roundhead) triumph, widely regarded as the decisive turning point in the protracted [English Civil War](/English_Civil_War). This conflict, a series of bitter struggles, unfolded across the lands of [England and Wales](/Kingdom_of_England), with repercussions even reaching the nascent [English American](/British_America) colonies, from August 1642 to September 1651. Its conclusion marked an unequivocal [Parliamentarian](/Roundhead) victory, fundamentally reshaping the political and religious landscape of the [British Isles](/British_Isles).

